sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant GHA as GitHub Actions/Konflux
    participant RedHat as Red Hat Registry<br/>UBI Base Images
    participant Quay as Quay.io<br/>quay.io/opendatahub/workbench-images<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant IS as OpenShift ImageStream
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Notebook Controller
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>Sidecar
    participant Notebook as JupyterLab Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant PyPI as PyPI.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over Dev,Quay: Flow 1: Image Build and Deployment
    Dev->>GHA: Push code to GitHub<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.3<br/>GitHub Token
    GHA->>RedHat: Pull UBI base images<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Registry Token
    RedHat-->>GHA: Base image
    GHA->>GHA: Build notebook image
    GHA->>Quay: Push built image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Quay Token
    Quay-->>IS: Image available<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Pull Secret
    K8sAPI->>IS: Create ImageStream<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Pod Launch
    User->>Dashboard: Select notebook image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>OAuth Token
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch Notebook CR
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pod/Service/Route<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Kubelet->>Quay: Pull image from ImageStream<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Pull Secret
    Quay-->>Kubelet: Notebook image
    Kubelet->>Notebook: Start JupyterLab container
    User->>OAuth: Access notebook<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>OAuth Token
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth token
    OAuth->>Notebook: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>Proxied auth
    Notebook-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI
    OAuth-->>User: JupyterLab interface

    Note over User,PyPI: Flow 3: Runtime Package Installation
    User->>Notebook: Execute: pip install <package>
    Notebook->>PyPI: GET /simple/<package><br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>No auth
    PyPI-->>Notebook: Package archive
    Notebook->>Notebook: Install package

    Note over Notebook,KFP: Flow 4: Data Science Workflow
    Notebook->>S3: Read training data<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS IAM Keys (Boto3)
    S3-->>Notebook: Dataset
    Notebook->>DB: Query data<br/>PostgreSQL/5432 TLS<br/>Username/Password
    DB-->>Notebook: Results
    Notebook->>Notebook: Train model
    Notebook->>S3: Save model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS IAM Keys
    Notebook->>K8sAPI: Submit KFP pipeline<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KFP: Pipeline definition
    Notebook->>KFP: Submit via Elyra<br/>HTTP/8888 HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
    KFP-->>Notebook: Pipeline run ID
